definitions.definition: To make necessary ; to behove ; to require (something) to be brought about .
examples: The early departure of her plane necessitated her waking up at 4 a.m.

definitions.definition: To force into a certain course of action; compel .

main_definition: ( transitive ) To make necessary ; to behove ; to require (something) to be brought about . [from early 17th c.]
secondary_definitions: ( of circumstances ) To force into a certain course of action; compel .
